      • main

        public static void main(String[] args)
                 throws IOException,
                        XMLStreamException,
                        SBMLException
        Reads the file that is passed as argument and write it to the console, using the method SBMLWriter.write(SBMLDocument, java.io.OutputStream).
        Parameters:
        args - the command line arguments, we are taking the first one as the file name to read.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the file name is not valid.
        SBMLException - if there are any problems reading or writing the SBML model.
        XMLStreamException - if there are any problems reading or writing the XML file.
